  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help small cocoa farmers make a living</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project works with isolated communities located on small islands in the Pacific Rim of Fire heavily affected by Climate Change. The project will provide a sustainable livelihood for over 1,000 farmers, assisting over 5,000 men, women and children.
Ni-Vanuatu cocoa growers are facing serious challenges to make an income to cover daily expenses and pay for school fees for their children. The project will train them to upgrade product quality and yield and will give them access to market.</narrative>
  </description>
